Project - Group 16


To compile the project type "make" in the terminal


Firstly run ./ES [-p ESport] [-v], 
where: 
ESport is the well-known port where the ES server accepts requests, both in UDP and TCP. 
This is an optional argument. If omitted, it assumes the value 58000+GN, where GN is the number of the group.

Then run ./user [-n ESIP] [-p ESport], 
where: 
ESIP is the IP address of the machine where the Event Reservation Server (ES) runs. 
This is an optional argument. If this argument is omitted, the ES should be running on the same machine. 
ESport is the well-known port (TCP and UDP) where the ES accepts requests. This is an optional argument. 
If omitted, it assumes the value 58000+GN, where GN is the group number.
